BFN 

  [Summary] "This morning, 27 May, the Ninth National 
Assembly's fifth session continued at the conference hall under 
the direction of Vice Chairman Phung Van Tuu. After listening 
to the National Assembly's Secretariat reading a summary of the 
deputies' suggestions on the labor code draft, the National 
Assembly deputies contributed their opinions on the first 
chapter of the draft". 
  The deputies discussed the minimum working age, bonuses, and 
other entitlements and issues related to laborers. 
  "In the afternoon, after the report by Tran Dinh Hoan, 
minister of labor, war invalids, and social welfare, the 
deputies continued to tender their opinions on other chapters of 
the draft", discussing such issues as the name of the law, the 
working age, severance pay, retrenchment pay, and so forth. 
  Tomorrow morning the deputies will continue to discuss the 
labor code draft. 

