  [Excerpt] Cambodia's elder statesman has emphasised that 
he opposes a proposal for military assistance to the Cambodian 
army. 
  "Samdech Son Sann does not support military assistance to 
the 
Cambodian Army as he has always believed that it serves only to 
prolong the war," his assistant, Son Chhai, said in a statement. 
  The statement came after Son Sann was reported to have 
expressed support for Thailand's position on Cambodia including 
the matter of military aid. 
  Thailand has repeatedly made clear that it is against 
military help for the Cambodian army. [passage omitted] 

