<H3> <TI>   Tokyo Official Predicts Sea of Japan Missile Test </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo Official Predicts Sea of Japan Missile Test </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3005051794 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 29 May 94 
Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3005051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A senior Japanese Foreign Ministry official 
disclosed on 28 May that the DPRK [Democratic People's Republic 
of Korea] plans to carry out missile test launches over the Sea 
of Japan in a few days. 
  This information is the result of the analysis of data 
provided by the United States. He said, "Preparations for the 
experiment are under way. We have concluded that it will be 
carried out in the immediate future." 
  The Japanese Government was able to confirm the test 
launches 
of the DPRK's "Nodong-1" ballistic missile in May 1993. It 
believes that the missile to be tested this time will be 
slightly bigger and that it will have a greater range. 

</TEXT>

