<H3> <TI>   LDP's Kono Asks Hata To Resign Before Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    LDP's Kono Asks Hata To Resign Before Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3105051094 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 May 
94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3105051094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yohei Kono, president of the Liberal Democratic 
Party [LDP], gave a speech in Niigata City on 29 May, in which 
he said, "What can (Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata's) minority 
government promise when it goes to the meeting of leaders of the 
advanced nations (the Naples Summit)? If something is agreed 
upon at the summit, will it be able to implement it? We have to 
think about whom we should send out as a responsible 
representative to the international community." He indicated 
that the Hata cabinet should resign before the summit is held on 
8 July. 

</TEXT>

