<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   DSP's Ouchi on Role of Kaishin in Realignment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DSP's Ouchi on Role of Kaishin in Realignment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3105100594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 May 
94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW3105100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Keigo Ouchi, chairman of the Democratic Socialist 
Party [DSP], delivered a speech in Morioka City on 29 May, in 
which he commented on the "Kaishin" parliamentary group in the 
House of Representatives, the formation of which triggered the 
Social Democratic Party of Japan's secession from the coalition 
government. He said, "While this group is being criticized, from 
a long-term point of view, it will prove to be useful (for the 
realignment of the political world)." He thus stressed the 
significance of the group's formation. 
  Ouchi held an informal meeting with reporters after the 
speech. Asked about demands inside the DSP and from labor unions 
supporting DSP for his resignation as chairman, Ouchi said, "I 
will have to reach a conclusion before the party convention (to 
be held on 7 and 8 June)." 

</TEXT>

